args: Cry all ya want, little miss! Ain't\nnobody gonna swoop in and save ya.
Yer fate's been sealed since ya laid eyes\non us doin' our work, y'see. Can't have you\nrunnin' around squawkin' our secrets.
Chitose? That eyesore of a kid? Put a\nfork in 'im, 'cause he's done for. He ain't\ncomin', no matter how much ya wail.
And now, I's gonna send ya right along to\nmeet yer precious little Chitose in heaven!\nDIE!
It won't be that easy, I'm afraid!
In this world, evil never pays,\nand cuteness always prevails!
Hark, for I am justice, adorned with a bow!\nNo river nor valley can stand in my way!\nNow, cease your villainy, you...villains!
Still alive, huh? Pretty dumb move\nto come here alone! Get 'im, boys!
Damn you! But give it up—\nyer completely outnumbered!
*wheeze* It's like I kicked a beehive!\nThere's no end to this swarm of jerks!
Hmph. If you plant that sweet little face'a\nyours at our feet and beg forgiveness,\nI'm willin' to kill you quickly!
You got another thing coming if you think\nI'm gonna be begging for mer—GWAAAH!
Bah ha ha! Ya talk a mean game, but yer\njust a little punk! Now, say yer prayers!
*sigh* You call this buying time? Shoulda\nlet me do it. Just barely got here in time.
Obviously. I'm a consummate professional.\nI've got the whole gang here. Now, sic 'em,\nfolks!
Yeah! Let's go, everyone!\nLet's save Chitose!
Eyagh! Who the hell are all these punks?!
Oh, y'know, just diehard Chitose fans!
Urk... What the HELL is goin' on here?!\nHurry up and DO something, you lot!
We can't, boss! Th-there're so many folks\nsquirmin' around that we can't move!
Hee hee hee! The power of my cuteness\nis the most magnetic force in the world!\nSurely even you can feel it, no? *wink*

The hell kinda new age crap're you
spoutin'?! You got a screw loose, kid!
I don't care how many peasants you
dredge up, I've still got the girl—
What?! Sh-she's gone?! HEY! MINIONS!\nWhere's the damn girl?!
Vice saved her while you were focused on\nthe townspeople.
And now, it's time for you to pay the piper!\nBe a good boy and let us tie you up, 'kay?
Grrr! Shut the hell up! You think I'm\njust gonna roll over like a damn dog?!

Oooh, watch out, folks. We've got
a tough guy here. I guess that means
you're DYING to see my trump card!
Prepare to be dazzled!
Everybody, we can't just stand here!\nWe gotta support Chitose, too!

Chitose, Chitose, he's our man!
If he can't do it, no one can!
You're so cute it makes us blush!
Turn this jerk's face into mush!
I get my own cheer? Score!\nAll right, let's do this!\nTime to break some boundaries!
Tee hee. Who needs a wrecking ball\nwhen I'm around?
I believe in my cuteness, and my fans do,\ntoo. And that makes me invincible!\n*beam*
I don't get it, but... Urgh. We totally lost.
Total defeat...by the power of cuteness...
Are you okay? I was so worried!
Yeah. I'm okay because I believed\nin you! Thank you for saving me.
You really are amazing, Chitose.\nI want to be just like you.
I hope I can be as cute as you someday.
Yeah. Just so long as you believe in your\nown cuteness—your own feelings.

I'm living proof of that. I decided that
no matter what other people expected
from me, I'd always be true to myself
when I grew up—my unique, adorable self.

All you need to do is listen to your heart.
If you do, I'm sure you'll be giving even
me a run for my money one of these days!
Because cuteness is what? Justice! *wink*

Okay! I'll use you as a role model
and learn everything there is to know!
You know why, Vice? Because cuteness
is justice! *wink*
Ugh, I hear that enough coming from\nTHIS guy. Don't point your love beams\nor whatever at me, too.
You're such a party pooper, Vice!\nYou really don't see Chitose's appeal?
Dunno. More importantly, if we're done\nhere, let's escort the people back to town.\nAll right, folks, time to go!
Phew, what a relief. They didn't find out.
I can never tell them how I got swept\nup in the moment and started cheering\nalong with the crowd...
And that's my report, Lady Mitsuhide.\nThe exchange with Alberia is going well,\nand the girl I saved is doing even better.
Nice work. I knew I was right to put you\nin charge of networking with other nations.
Hee hee. I couldn't have done\nit without you, Lady Mitsuhide.
Lemme just say this: becoming an adult\ndoesn't mean letting go of who you are.
What got you so hung up on the idea\nthat you'd suddenly lose your cuteness\nupon growing up?
If you hadn't talked some sense into me,\nI would have given up on being cute.

It's no exaggeration to say that my
cuteness diplomacy's success and
the little girl's rescue are all thanks
to you, Lady Mitsuhide.
I said that stuff? Huh. Well, I'm glad.\nY'know, that you can still be cute and all.
Yeah! And that's why I'm gonna keep\nbusting my cute little butt to repay the\nfavor!
No matter the task, just leave it to me:\nyour #1 most adorable ambassador!
